Treasury Says S&P Action Shows Congress Must Act Expeditiously

-- B y   I a n   K a t z   a n d   C h e y e n n e   H o p k i n s
-- 
2011-07-14T23:51:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/treasury-says-s-p-action-shows-congress-must-act-expeditiously.html
Standard & Poor’s Rating Services’s
announcement that the U.S. may have its credit ratings cut shows
that Congress “must act expeditiously to avoid defaulting on
the country’s obligations,” Treasury Undersecretary for
Domestic Finance Jeffrey Goldstein said in a statement today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
